Brute Force : T.C. - O(N), S.C. - O(N) 
My approach : I couldn't remember build in functions like isalnum(), reverse string function like (::-1) that made
me close to the answer but not to the code

class Solution:
    def isPalindrome(self, s: str) -> bool:
        newStr = ''
        for c in s:
            if c.isalnum():
                newStr += c.lower()
        return newStr == newStr[::-1]        

Optimal : T.C. - O(N), S.C. - O(1)
MY approach: When you have to check in array from the last to the start but want less space (don't want to make
a new array) use two pointer which takes two pointer from start to the end

class Solution:
    def isPalindrome(self, s: str) -> bool:
        l, r = 0, len(s)-1

        while l<r:
            while l<r and not s[l].isalnum():
                l += 1
            while r>l and not s[r].isalnum():
                r -= 1
            if s[l].lower() != s[r].lower():
                return False
            l, r = l+1, r-1
        return True

